body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello! Thank you for contacting Sanders Automotive, my name is Gary Sanders. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Kelly Diaz.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Kelly. Can you please provide me with your contact number without including any dashes or spaces?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my contact number is five five five one two three four.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you! And for verification purposes, could you confirm the first four digits of your home address in a descriptive manner?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: The first four digits of my address are seven three eight zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information, Kelly. Is there anything else you would like to discuss or inquire about today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I just wanted to inquire about the pricing for the new models.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for bringing that up, Kelly. I will provide you with the necessary details. Thank you for your time and have a wonderful day!
